<!-- SLIDE 4: What is BVIF? -->
<section class="slide" data-notes="Now that you have seen what BVIF can do, let's explain what it is. BVIF is a systematic framework for turning an AI initiative into a quantified business value evaluation. Starting from a plain-language description of the initiative, it guides you — through an agent — through defining the right metrics, assessing how feasibly each can be measured, collecting data, and calculating an annualized business value that is grounded in evidence and traceable end-to-end. It is organized into three phases and seven stages. Discovery (blue): stages 1–2 define the initiative and map it to business value categories. Metrics (green): stages 3–4 identify candidate metrics, assess feasibility (F1/F2/F3), and adjust based on data availability. Quantification (orange): stages 5–7 collect data, calculate the annualized value, and produce the final results document. Every stage ends with an approval gate — the agent never advances without your explicit OK — and every user interaction and answer is captured in sequentially numbered files, so nothing gets lost.">
  <span class="eyebrow">What is BVIF?</span>
  <h2 class="headline">From a plain-language AI idea to quantified value</h2>

  <p style="max-width:1100px; font-size:18px; color:var(--ink); margin-bottom: 18px;">
    A systematic framework that guides you through defining metrics, assessing feasibility,
    collecting data, and calculating annualized value — <span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:700;">grounded in evidence, traceable end-to-end.</span>
  </p>

  <div class="phase-band">
    <div class="phase discover">🔵  Discovery</div>
    <div class="phase metrics">🟢  Metrics</div>
    <div class="phase quant">🟡  Quantification</div>
  </div>

  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step" style="border-color: rgba(31,155,255,0.5);"><div class="num">1</div><div class="lbl">Define the initiative</div><div style="font-size:11px; color:var(--accent); margin-top:6px;">← Start — The idea</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="num">2</div><div class="lbl">Extract business value categories</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="num">3</div><div class="lbl">Identify metrics</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="num">4</div><div class="lbl">Adjust for feasibility</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="num">5</div><div class="lbl">Collect data</div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="num">6</div><div class="lbl">Calculate business value</div></div>
    <div class="step" style="border-color: rgba(255,153,0,0.5);"><div class="num">7</div><div class="lbl">Final results</div><div style="font-size:11px; color:var(--accent); margin-top:6px;">End — Quantified business value →</div></div>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top:28px; display:flex; gap:14px; justify-content:center;">
    <span class="chip" style="background: rgba(31,155,255,0.12); color:#7ec3ff; border-color: rgba(31,155,255,0.35);">Approval gates at every stage</span>
    <span class="chip" style="background: rgba(38,194,129,0.12); color:#6be0a7; border-color: rgba(38,194,129,0.35);">Full audit trail</span>
    <span class="chip">Works from business context alone</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SLIDE 5: What you will do today -->
