<!-- SLIDE 6: Pre-work -->
<section class="slide" data-notes="Before we start the hands-on portion, there are two things each team needs to do. Business side: read the Precision Furniture storyline from bvif-samples/bvif-scenarios/scenario_A-Manufacturing-company/. It is a few pages long and covers the company, the executives, the operational metrics, and the initiative. Hint — use AI (any assistant you prefer) to query the document rather than reading it cover to cover. Tech side: clone the repository from GitLab AWS. That repo has the Kiro steering files, the rule details, and the sample run you saw earlier. Read the README — it explains how to open the workspace in Kiro and what to expect. You have 30 minutes for pre-work. If you hit snags, flag us — better to resolve them now than during the workshop itself.">
  <span class="eyebrow">Workshop · Part 2</span>
  <h2 class="headline">Pre-work</h2>

  <div class="row" style="gap:24px; flex:1; align-items:stretch;">
    <div class="col card">
      <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:10px;">
        <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 36 36"><circle cx="18" cy="18" r="17" fill="none" stroke="#ff9900" stroke-width="2"/><text x="18" y="23" text-anchor="middle" fill="#ff9900" font-weight="800" font-size="16">B</text></svg>
        <h3 style="color:var(--ink); font-size:22px;">Business side</h3>
      </div>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>Read the Precision Furniture storyline</li>
        <li>Use AI to query the document — do not read it cover to cover</li>
        <li>Focus on: company profile, execs, metrics, the initiative</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col card">
      <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:10px;">
        <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 36 36"><circle cx="18" cy="18" r="17" fill="none" stroke="#1f9bff" stroke-width="2"/><text x="18" y="23" text-anchor="middle" fill="#1f9bff" font-weight="800" font-size="16">T</text></svg>
        <h3 style="color:var(--ink); font-size:22px;">Tech side</h3>
