</section>

<!-- SLIDE 7: Run the session -->
<section class="slide" data-notes="How to run the BVIF session. Open your Kiro workspace and, in the chat, type: 'Run a business value identification for [explain the AI initiative]'. Replace the brackets with the initiative you are evaluating — for the workshop, use the Precision Furniture predictive maintenance idea. From there, follow the guidance Kiro gives you. A few practical notes. First: provide your answers in files, not in chat. Kiro will create sequentially numbered interaction files (like 01-session-setup-questions.md) in each stage folder. Open them, answer inline, save, and tell Kiro you are done. Push back when Kiro gets something wrong — this is a conversation, not a form. Second: every artifact is a markdown file. Use Kiro's built-in preview (the eye icon or Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+V) for readability. Third: in Stage 5 (data collection), you can either answer inline or upload a file. If you upload, put it in the `uploads/` folder under stage 05. For the workshop you can build your own data file from the storyline — try both paths with different teams. Finally: if Kiro offers to move this into Spec mode at any point, politely decline. BVIF has its own workflow.">
