<!-- SLIDE 11: Appendix — How steering works -->
<section class="slide" data-notes="Appendix A — how the steering works. You do not need this to run BVIF, but it helps to understand what is happening under the hood. The file `.kiro/steering/bvif-rules/core-workflow.md` is loaded as an always-included steering rule. It defines the BVIF phases and stages and tells the agent to load supporting files from `.kiro/bvif-rule-details/` on demand. Outputs go into a `bvif-docs/` folder at the workspace root. Each initiative gets its own subfolder — the agent asks you for the initiative name, builds a short slug, and creates `bvif-docs/<NN>-<slug>-<yyyymm>/`. All artifacts for that initiative — the state file, the audit log, every stage subfolder — live inside that per-initiative folder. `<NN>` is a zero-padded counter starting at 01 that increments with each new initiative. `<yyyymm>` is the year and month when the initiative was started. This means you can run multiple BVIF sessions in the same workspace without artifacts colliding.">
  <span class="eyebrow">Appendix A</span>
  <h2 class="headline">How the steering works</h2>

  <div class="row" style="flex:1; gap:22px; align-items:stretch;">
    <div class="col card">
      <span class="pill">Steering rule</span>
      <h3 style="color:var(--ink); font-size:18px; margin-top:8px;">.kiro/steering/bvif-rules/core-workflow.md</h3>
      <p style="font-size:14px;">Always-included. Defines the 7-stage workflow and tells the agent when to load supporting files.</p>

      <div style="margin-top:14px;">
        <span class="pill" style="background: rgba(38,194,129,0.15); color:#6be0a7; border-color: rgba(38,194,129,0.35);">Loaded on demand</span>
        <h3 style="color:var(--ink); font-size:18px; margin-top:8px;">.kiro/bvif-rule-details/</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14px;">Stage-specific guidance, question templates, process overview.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col card" style="flex:1.2;">
      <span class="pill">Output structure</span>
      <pre style="margin-top:10px; font-size:12.5px; line-height:1.6; color: var(--ink-dim); background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25); padding: 16px; border-radius: 10px; overflow:auto;">
bvif-docs/
└── <span style="color:var(--accent);">01-customer-churn-predictor-202604/</span>
    ├── 00-session-setup/
    ├── 01-initiative-definition/
    ├── 02-business-value-mapping/
    ├── 03-metrics-identification/
    ├── 04-metrics-adjustment/
    ├── 05-data-collection/
    │   └── uploads/
    ├── 06-business-value-calculation/
    ├── 07-final-results/
    ├── bvif-state.md
    └── audit.md</pre>
      <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:10px;">
        <span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:700;">&lt;NN&gt;</span> = running counter ·
        <span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:700;">&lt;slug&gt;</span> = short initiative name ·
        <span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:700;">&lt;yyyymm&gt;</span> = start date
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SLIDE 12: Appendix — BVIF scenarios & samples -->
<section class="slide" data-notes="Appendix B — BVIF scenarios and samples. The `bvif-samples/` folder in the repo is organized to hold multiple scenarios over time. Each scenario lives in its own subfolder under `bvif-samples/bvif-scenarios/`. Today we have Scenario A — Precision Furniture Inc. — but additional scenarios may be added in the future. The `bvif-samples/bvif-docs/` folder contains the reference run artifacts (the completed output) for Scenario A. It shows every interaction file, every approval, the audit log, and the final results document — the same document that produced the $9.36M result we saw earlier. Use it as a reference only. Your execution will be different, and that is okay. We actively want to see different experiences and different results — that is how we validate the framework across teams and styles. Do not treat it as an answer key.">
  <span class="eyebrow">Appendix B</span>
